### Oficios UY API Tests
### Base URL
@baseUrl = https://localhost:5001/api/v1

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Juan Pérez",
  "email": "juan@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "user"
}

### 2. Register a provider
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Carlos Electricista",
  "email": "carlos@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "provider"
}

### 3. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Get current user (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

### 5. Get all services
GET {{baseUrl}}/services

### 6. Create a service (requires provider role)
POST {{baseUrl}}/services
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Instalación Eléctrica Residencial",
  "description": "Instalación completa de sistemas eléctricos para hogares",
  "category": "Electricidad",
  "priceRange": "$2000 - $5000"
}

### 7. Create a booking (requires authentication)
POST {{baseUrl}}/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serviceId": 1,
  "dateRequested": "2024-02-15T10:00:00Z"
}

### 8. Get user bookings (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}/bookings/user/1

### 9. Get user by ID (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/1

### 10. Update user (requires authentication)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Juan Pérez Updated",
  "email": "juan.updated@example.com"
}

### 11. Refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh

### 12. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
